Good offices: Facilitate an inclusive political, security and economic dialogue through engagement with Libyan institutions, political parties, and civil society, including women and youth. Support military unification efforts, including disarmament, demobilization and reintegration and strategic security frameworks (20 beneficiaries); 
Advance ceasefire implementation through monthly meetings of the 5+5 Joint Military Commission and Liaison Subcommittees (12–15 key actors), maintaining a database on foreign fighters, and conducting four capacity-building workshops for international monitors and Libyan subcommittees in 2025; 
Engage with CSOs, women and youth (YouEngage) in four workshops to promote ceasefire implementation; 
Support transitional justice and accountability through technical advice and capacity building for 100 lawyers, prosecutors, and judges. Strengthen the judiciary with digital modernization efforts and best practices in post-conflict accountability;
Promote women’s rights in line with the Convention on the Elimination of All Forms of Discrimination advocating for institutional protections, access to justice, and mechanisms for survivors of violence and support women’s empowerment units in security institutions and elections bodies.

