	Consultation, advice and advocacy: Support Libya’s political process through electoral assistance, constitution-making advice, and coordination with international partners (100 beneficiaries). Provide daily technical guidance to the High National Elections Commission, strengthening electoral management, and advising on electoral dispute resolution and security planning;
Advise the 5+5 Joint Military Commission and the Libyan-led and Libyan-owned ceasefire monitoring mechanism, on legal and security frameworks, including capacity-building;
Support Libyan Mine Action Centre and partners on arms control, clearance of explosives remnants of war and ammunition management; organize Mine Action Day event with 50 stakeholders;
Advance inclusive, victim-centred and rights-based national reconciliation through workshops and seminars reaching 50 beneficiaries confidence-building sessions with 50 participants from national and local authorities, and civil society organizations;
Promote human rights through implementation of due diligence policy, civic space advocacy, and coordination with four local justice institutions (30 participants), including the Ministry of Justice, the Ministry of Interior, the prosecutor’s office and the High Judicial Council, for the release of individuals detained without a legal basis;
Support the Libyan Political Dialogue Forum and House of Representatives women’s caucus and civil society and women’s groups, reaching approximately 500 women;
Establish an advocacy plan for the law on violence against women; establish the National Consultation Groups as part of Monitoring, Analysis and Reporting Arrangements (MARA) and Conflict-Related Sexual Violence setting; 
Support security sector governance, reform and development, including reintegration of non-State armed groups and supporting the increased presence of women in the police force; 
Advocate for women’s rights by facilitating discussions among institutions and actors working on women’s rights and advising on laws and policies that promote gender equality; advice on violence against women and gender-based violence linked to the electoral process;
Support reinforcing the capacity of 30 human rights defenders and women human rights defenders on the Monitoring, Analysis and Reporting Arrangements Technical Working Group; 
Advocate for the rights and protection of migrants and asylum-seekers and their access to justice, accountability and redress mechanisms, regardless of status; and advocacy and capacity-building to amplify the voices of young people and their meaningful participation in reconciliation efforts and political processes.

